<subSubSection pageId="159" pageNumber="437" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="159.[789,1381,1996,2420]" lastBlockId="159.[174,1380,2425,2813]" pageId="159" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[790,1039,2233,2262]" pageId="159" pageNumber="437">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 72-97 mm, tail 74—108 mm, ear 12-18 mm, hindfoot 20-24 mm; weight 12-22 g (mean 17 g). The Narrow-footed Bristly Mouse is small, with tail longer than head-body length and distinctly bicolored, at least near base, with small caudal scales. Hindfoot has long outer digits. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 35-36, FN = 40.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
